assembly_info.comments:
Salmonella enterica subspecies enterica serovar Infantis strain SARB27 was obtained from the collection of Selander (J. General Microbiology (1993), 139:1125-32; PMID: 8360609). SARB27 is a rare multilocus enzyme electrophoresis (MLEE) variant within serovar Infantis, called In3, occurring once within a collection of 110 isolates of this serovar. This strain was isolated in Senegal from an unknown source, prior to 1993. These authors serotyped the strain as 6,7:r:1,5. The sequenced strain was deposited in ATCC as BAA-1675. The strain was selected for sequencing due to its divergence from other strains classified as Infantis (J. Bacteriol. (2004) 186:5883-98; PMID: 15317794).

This is an improved assembly with seven ordered contigs and one plasmid (pSEENIN0B).

The genome was sequenced to a depth of 21.59X. The whole-genome shotgun plasmid and 454 reads were assembled using PCAP assembler.

Assembly name: Salmonella_enterica_SARB27-2.0.

Coding sequences were predicted using GeneMark v3.3 and Glimmer3 v3.02. Intergenic regions not spanned by GeneMark and Glimmer3 were blasted against NCBI's non-redundant (NR) database and predictions generated based on protein alignments. tRNA genes were determined using tRNAscan-SE 1.23 and non-coding RNA genes by RNAmmer-1.2 and Rfam v8.1. The final gene set is processed through several programs such as Kegg (Release 56), psortB (Version 3.0.3) and Interproscan (Version 4.7) to determine possible function. Gene product names are determined by BER (Version 2.5). Gene names are generated at the contig level and may not necessarily reflect any known order or orientation between contigs.
